sequenceDiagram
  autonumber

  participant U as 👤 User
  participant WC as 🌐 Web Client
  participant GW as ⚡ API Gateway<br/>(server.mjs)
  participant HG as 🔀 Hermes Gateway<br/>(Kanban / SQLite)
  participant TR as 🖊 Translator<br/>(Opus 4)
  participant PH as ⚗ Philosophers<br/>(Wittgenstein · Quine · Frege)
  participant CS as 🗳 Consensus<br/>(2-of-3 vote)
  participant FS as 📁 Filesystem<br/>(corpus/runs/)
  participant SC as 🔬 Scientists<br/>(Koehn · Cho · Vaswani)

  rect rgb(14, 20, 40)
    note over U,FS: PHASE 1 — Submission & Setup
    U->>WC: Paste segments · click Translate
    WC->>GW: POST /runs  { segments: [...], client: "<client-id>" }
    activate GW
    GW->>FS: mkdir corpus/runs/YYYY-MM-DD_NNN/<br/>write source/segments.json
    GW->>HG: hermes kanban create<br/>--assignee translator
    GW-->>WC: 202 Accepted  { run_id, ws_url }
    deactivate GW
    WC->>GW: WebSocket connect  ws://localhost:3000/runs/:id
    note right of WC: Client now listens for<br/>progress events via WS
  end

  rect rgb(14, 30, 22)
    note over HG,FS: PHASE 2 — Translation (Hot Path · Step 1)
    HG->>TR: dispatch task: translate
    activate TR
    TR->>FS: read source/segments.json
    TR->>FS: write final/translation_draft.json
    deactivate TR
    FS-->>GW: fs.watch() fires on file change
    GW-->>WC: WS event  agent_done { agent: "translator", progress: 25% }
  end

  rect rgb(40, 28, 8)
    note over HG,FS: PHASE 3 — Philosophical Review (Hot Path · Step 2, parallel)
    HG->>PH: dispatch 3 tasks in parallel
    activate PH
    par Wittgenstein
      PH->>FS: read translation_draft.json
      PH->>FS: write final/critique_wittgenstein.json
      FS-->>GW: fs.watch() fires
      GW-->>WC: WS event  agent_done { agent: "wittgenstein", progress: 45% }
    and Quine
      PH->>FS: read translation_draft.json
      PH->>FS: write final/critique_quine.json
      FS-->>GW: fs.watch() fires
      GW-->>WC: WS event  agent_done { agent: "quine", progress: 55% }
    and Frege
      PH->>FS: read translation_draft.json
      PH->>FS: write final/critique_frege.json
      FS-->>GW: fs.watch() fires
      GW-->>WC: WS event  agent_done { agent: "frege", progress: 65% }
    end
    deactivate PH
  end

  rect rgb(40, 10, 10)
    note over CS,FS: PHASE 4 — Consensus Vote
    CS->>FS: read critique_wittgenstein.json<br/>read critique_quine.json<br/>read critique_frege.json
    activate CS

    alt 2+ Approve (happy path)
      CS->>FS: write consensus/verdict.json  { result: "approve" }
      CS-->>GW: verdict: approve
      GW-->>WC: WS event  consensus_reached { verdict: "approve", progress: 75% }
    else Revise (loop — max 3 rounds)
      CS->>FS: write consensus/verdict.json  { result: "revise", notes: [...] }
      CS-->>HG: re-queue translator with feedback
      note over HG,CS: Revision loop repeats<br/>up to 3 rounds
    else Block (human escalation)
      CS->>FS: write consensus/verdict.json  { result: "block" }
      CS-->>GW: verdict: block → human review required
      GW-->>WC: WS event  escalation_required
    end
    deactivate CS
  end

  rect rgb(14, 20, 40)
    note over GW,FS: PHASE 5 — Artifact Generation
    GW->>FS: generate final/review.html<br/>(bilingual EN · DE + critic panel)
    GW->>FS: html-to-pdf → final/review.pdf
    FS-->>GW: pdf ready
    GW-->>WC: WS event  artifact_ready { format: "pdf", progress: 95% }
    GW-->>WC: WS event  run_complete { status: "done", progress: 100% }
  end

  rect rgb(14, 20, 40)
    note over U,FS: PHASE 6 — Download
    U->>WC: Click Download PDF
    WC->>GW: GET /runs/:id/artifact?format=pdf
    GW-->>WC: 200  application/pdf  (review.pdf)
    WC-->>U: File download complete
  end

  rect rgb(10, 30, 22)
    note over SC,FS: PHASE 7 — Async Science Audits (post-merge · cron-triggered)
    note over SC: These run independently after<br/>the run is merged to corpus.<br/>They do NOT block delivery.
    SC->>FS: Koehn: git diff → detect skill regression
    SC->>FS: Cho: read MEMORY.md → cross-agent integrity
    SC->>FS: Vaswani: token audit → prune skills / identity drift
    SC->>FS: write feedback/ reports
  end
